data.title: Miami Central's James Cook, Dalvin's younger brother, commits to Florida State
data.meta_description: It will be until 2019 when he gets to make it official. But James Cook could not wait any longer. Cook — a promising Miami Central running back just like his older brother, Florida State running back Dalvin Cook — committed to the Seminoles’ 2019 recruiting class on Friday.
data.text:
It will be until 2019 when he gets to make it official.

But James Cook could not wait any longer.

Cook — a promising Miami Central running back just like his older brother, Florida State running back Dalvin Cook — committed to the Seminoles’ 2019 recruiting class on Friday.

I feel like it was the right move,” he said when confirming the commitment to the Tallahassee Democrat.

Cook becomes FSU’s first pledge for the Class of 2019.

And just like his brother did during an ESPN announcement, Cook tweeted he committed to the “University of Florida State” before changing it.

Cook has become one of the top high school freshmen in the country and gained deserved attention after a helping Miami Central win a state title in December with an impressive performance, carrying the ball 15 times for 178 yards and three touchdowns.

RELATED: James Cook has the all makings of a star

He was one of several freshmen to visit FSU for the team’s junior day recruiting event on Feb. 20, and named FSU his top school after the visit.

“It’s like family,” Cook said. “They bring you close together like I’m a player at Florida State already.”
